                   <h3 class="activity-heading-1 heading-color-adjustment">Retrofit Your Home - Apartment</h3>
                   <p>Think about new design possibilities and fill the blanks with your brilliant ideas about retrofitting this building
                     (hints are given by lines connecting to the installations)</p>
                    <br>
                    <img src="/media/images/apartment.png" width=100%>
                    <br>
                    <br>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">1.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Solar orientation - south facing roofs can take full advantage of sun.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">2.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Daylighting - salvaged wood sunscreens cotrol the sun's heat gain and maximize the daylight that the building can harvest.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">3.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Salvaged material - 50% of the building is made from salvaged materials which diverted about 160 tons of materials from going into a landfill.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">4.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Geothermal wells - allowing building to be 55% more efficient.
                        Read more <a href="https://www.cleanenergybc.org/about/clean-energy-sectors/geothermal">here</a>.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">5.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Pumps and geo-exchange. Heat pumps can take heat from the air or ground and use it to provide space hear or hot water.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">6.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Rooftop production garden - plants evaporation and shading wil lower the building temperature.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">7.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Greywater reuse for toilet. Rainwater cistern conserves 60% of building water.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">8.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Vinyl window with low-E glass. Keep warm air in during the winter and hot solar rays out during the summer.
                      Read more <a href="https://energy.gov/energysaver/energy-efficient-windows">here</a>.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">9.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Bicycle parking - encourage active transportation.</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="collapsible"><h4 class="heading-color-adjustment">10.</h4></button>
                    <div class="content">
                      <p>Regenerative elevator.</p>
                    </div>



